Comment: 0,0:02:24.20,0:02:31.71,Sign,,0,0,0,,Original online game "Kingdom of Chaos" \Nhttp://www.if-kingdom.com/ \NPlanning and concept by Shingo Kuwana
Dialogue: 10,0:00:04.15,0:00:08.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Long ago, this world was a beautiful paradise.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:10.57,0:00:14.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In this world of balance, people, demons, and gods all feared and respected each other equally.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:14.78,0:00:21.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,All of them lived with the hope and belief\N that this way of life would last forever.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:23.79,0:00:25.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That was Neverland.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:26.83,0:00:31.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Situated in the southwestern part of the Old Continent was the mountain kingdom of Bjor.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:32.47,0:00:35.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The man who ascended as the thirteenth Generalissimo of Bjor, Fract,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:35.76,0:00:38.47,Narrator,,0,0,0,,turned this country \Ninto a warmongering nation.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:39.06,0:00:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Who if not we, the Bjor, deserves a place\N under the sun on top of the Old Continent?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:43.56,0:00:47.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He was a natural leader and politician, \Nso he took command of Bjor's army
Dialogue: 10,0:00:47.06,0:00:49.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and invaded Orthozes, \Na neighboring country in the north.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:55.61,0:00:59.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Although soundly defeated in his first campaign, \NFract profited from the experience.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:59.70,0:01:02.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He rebuilt his army the next year and
Dialogue: 10,0:01:02.00,0:01:04.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,moved into Harbus and Glok in the south.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:04.25,0:01:08.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And then on to Axes, Elflore, and Bihlimere.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:08.38,0:01:12.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Before people realized it,\N Bjor had occupied half of the continent.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:25.85,0:01:30.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This was the reality. An iron fist, ruling with brutality and fear.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:31.23,0:01:35.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Under Fract's rule, \Nthe Old Continent was soaked in blood.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.78,0:01:41.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Finally, to rectify his past failure, Fract prepared to invade the last country on his border,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.33,0:01:43.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the agricultural nation of Orthozes.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.79,0:01:47.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Rich in produce, \Nthis country was never at risk of famine.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:47.42,0:01:50.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was a rare place where all creatures\N lived in harmony with nature.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.42,0:01:56.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, all they could do now was wait,\N constantly in fear of Bjor's massed armies.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.59,0:02:01.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,One man's lust for power \Ndrags the world into chaos.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.89,0:02:05.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,History has taught us that power\N sustained by fear always leads to chaos.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.48,0:02:11.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This story is an episode from the lives\N of those who stood up against this power.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:57.86,0:04:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Generalissimo.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.15,0:05:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize for arriving so early.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.94,0:05:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw you from outside, so...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.95,0:05:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.49,0:05:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Our special border patrol unit\N will engage the enemy at nightfall. {lit: visit will be at night - no clue what she means, assuming they mean "will start a war at midnight" as in "special forces will come up with a casus beli", like germans did in operation konserve, as if "fuhrer" and the bjor symbol weren't clear enough cues}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.79,0:05:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm aware.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.87,0:05:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave that order myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.29,0:05:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. But your ministers want\N your personal confirmation,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.30,0:05:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because they haven't seen you \Nin person at all lately.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.64,0:05:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.72,0:05:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot afford to lose this next battle, either.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.85,0:05:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the process of formulating our tactics.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.31,0:05:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm... worried that if you overwork yourself, \Nit may damage your health.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.82,0:05:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Kanon, I have long sought to own Orthozes.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.74,0:05:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Our country is an infertile, \Nrocky mountain range.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.03,0:05:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What did the country right next to us do \Nto receive such abundant natural wealth?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:54.79,0:05:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I was jealous of that.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.83,0:06:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You already control many countries\N across this continent.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.92,0:06:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you still need to go after Orthozes?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.38,0:06:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it because that country was the only one\N that didn't bow to your father, the previous king?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.34,0:06:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep this conversation between us.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.35,0:06:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If I take Orthozes, I will be a king\N who surpasses my father.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:37.54,0:06:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I get excited when I see the border!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.92,0:06:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.67,0:06:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't look like you do.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:44.67,0:06:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? Well, I suppose you become tougher\N after you've been at war for as long as I have.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.38,0:06:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you always seem excited to me.\N That's what I mean.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.02,0:06:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.97,0:06:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you implying?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.19,0:07:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, {\i1}this{\i0}. {/there, see?}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:09.49,0:07:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.66,0:07:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We come from the mercenary headquarters\Nwith orders to reinforce the border guard.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.45,0:07:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Mara, and two others.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.41,0:07:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mara...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.71,0:07:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You mean {\i1}that{\i0} Mara?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.42,0:07:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon me. Please proceed.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.59,0:07:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.47,0:07:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I'm a bit famous too, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.18,0:07:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you just a mercenary like us?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.43,0:07:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I've also been doing this\N for a long time, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.48,0:07:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You must pay for the crimes\N you have committed.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.48,0:07:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My... crimes?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.43,0:08:16.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,It seems I fell asleep before finishing.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.43,0:08:21.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,To preserve at least my current self, \NI'm keeping a diary. {as in "to not forget who I am now"}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.60,0:08:25.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,To grasp some thread linking me to my past.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.53,0:08:39.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,That knight called Mara...\Nhas a big heart and a strong will.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.54,0:08:43.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,What could that leniency in her left eye mean? {believing the original sub, absolutely impossible to hear the word that's in her left eye, later it's revealed to be cybernetic as she lost her real eye on a training}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.60,0:09:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, move it!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.13,0:09:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't war, just a slaughter of the helpless.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:42.43,0:09:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.31,0:09:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hurry up and end this.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:28.35,0:10:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,C-Captain!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.23,0:10:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not your captain anymore.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.65,0:10:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So... you weren't even going\N to say goodbye to me?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.86,0:10:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.16,0:10:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I... thought you might be busy, so...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.70,0:10:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you come to dislike me? \NGo ahead, be honest.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:49.12,0:10:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would I...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:51.88,0:10:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the only one I could rely on. \NThat's why I called for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:57.38,0:11:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Since when have you had such a surprised face? {not sure what she means: slack; loose; lax; slovenly; sloppy}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.38,0:11:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to my office later.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.58,0:11:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, this is quite good. My usual morning\Ngruel is terrible, raw bugs and all. {hiyokomushi / ひよこ虫 - a mascot bug appearing is several works by idea factory (studio that made this); no idea about the first part of the sentence though}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.88,0:11:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Mara?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.38,0:11:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mara? Who knows?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:37.55,0:11:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems her previous regiment was stationed here, \Nso she probably knows a lot of local people.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.51,0:11:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Knows a lot of people?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.01,0:11:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You probably don't know anybody?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:50.06,0:11:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you did, you could find out\N about your past more easily.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.52,0:11:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Not knowing anyone at all is weird.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.45,0:12:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting today, the watch will be increased at all stations.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.41,0:12:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also a notice from headquarters.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.62,0:12:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Set a double watch on...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.46,0:12:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Set a double watch to respond\N to any situation.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.97,0:12:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.68,0:12:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Well, have a seat now.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.77,0:12:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So... what do you want?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:40.28,0:12:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The situation on the border\Nis tenser than ever. {/border conflicts}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.91,0:12:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We expect the Bjor forces to begin\N a full-scale invasion any time.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.49,0:12:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Their generalissimo
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.12,0:12:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,had long sought to occupy our country.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.79,0:12:54.46,Overlap,,0,0,0,,I've chosen a tough time...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.58,0:12:57.54,Overlap,,0,0,0,,to rejoin you. {lit: I've come at a difficult moment}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.00,0:13:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They've organized a special elite battalion, \Ntasked with wiping out our outpost.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.55,0:13:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They're planning a guerrilla operation. \NIs that why we're here?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.10,0:13:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. If the entire Crimson Knights regiment starts moving, they'll notice it at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.60,0:13:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We can only foil their plans \Nwith a tiny unit.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.81,0:13:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Mara, I'd like you to take on this assignment.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.19,0:13:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a dangerous mission, \Nso I'll have to confer with the others.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.24,0:13:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Mara, you haven't changed a bit.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.99,0:13:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm only asking you because of your talent.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.25,0:13:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You must understand, \Nyou didn't grow up on your own.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.04,0:13:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, who should be thanked \Nfor your upbringing?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.17,0:13:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You, Captain.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.88,0:13:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.05,0:13:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So will you do this for me?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.30,0:13:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.05,0:13:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.35,0:13:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Mara, I hope this war ends soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.11,0:14:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mara!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.96,0:14:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there you are!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.88,0:14:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.84,0:14:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Aide was worried about you.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.68,0:14:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? I'm touched.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.81,0:14:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No. I was just wondering\N what we're going to do next.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.94,0:14:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Just wait out time for a bit more here. \NI've got one more minor thing to see to.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.65,0:14:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I'm back, \Nwe're going to war!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.82,0:14:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, finally! \NTime to make some good money!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.53,0:14:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, war changes people, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.58,0:15:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, excuse me! \NI was like this before too.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.38,0:15:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.88,0:15:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Gimme a break!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.68,0:15:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Aide, did you need something from me?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.51,0:15:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.89,0:16:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What's his game, following Mara?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.35,0:16:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Mara will be Mara, \Nalways going alone.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.32,0:16:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Where'd he go?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:59.95,0:17:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.29,0:17:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I might've stumbled on something incredible!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.83,0:17:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It is an honor to have you here, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.22,0:18:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Generalissimo Fract came out here to commend you personally on your good work, Olb.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.31,0:18:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I-Is that true, sir?\N I am most honored, Generalissimo!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.10,0:18:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Generalissimo?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:10.81,0:18:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Diversionary sabotage from this front-line base will play a major role in the upcoming battle.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:16.78,0:18:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,United in their patriotism, the people of Orthozes\N will become a force to be reckoned with.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.58,0:18:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But thanks to your front line sabotage work, \Nthe enemy response will be disrupted.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.08,0:18:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In a war involving large armies, \Nboth sides are bound to sustain heavy casualties.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.09,0:18:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, I am moved by your\Nrespect for people's lives.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.26,0:18:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I respect people's lives?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.60,0:18:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir... Since you were concerned with both sides' losses...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.27,0:18:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All I want is the rich land of Orthozes.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.94,0:18:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of civilians killed doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.11,0:19:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir, roger that!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.66,0:19:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Up there!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.91,0:19:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.13,0:19:17.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,Aide?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.43,0:19:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there, get her!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.01,0:19:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Not so fast!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.17,0:20:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not getting away.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:08.27,0:20:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.19,0:20:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.24,0:20:27.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,Where did she go?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.63,0:20:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It would appear I can see more than you.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.68,0:20:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then. If you try something, you'll die here and now.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:55.44,0:20:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's coming to rescue you.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:00.94,0:21:04.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,While I'm risking my life here,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.24,0:21:08.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,Captain Cerona must still be\N profiting from the war,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:08.78,0:21:11.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,just like she did back then. {lit: make the war into business}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:11.50,0:21:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and get this over with,\N like you said you would! {very unsure, likely she actually says "even though she said she'd be done with it soon" but it makes 0 sense to worry about cerona right now}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.29,0:21:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Why are you in such a hu—
Dialogue: 10,0:21:25.76,0:21:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Mara, you'll be all right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.80,0:21:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Aide? But how?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.85,0:21:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I followed you.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:40.82,0:21:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess Dino did too.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:42.23,0:21:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Pretty much. I went after you, though, \Nso where the hell were you?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:47.78,0:21:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly opposite from where you were thrashing them.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.33,0:21:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I set out after Mara directly.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:54.50,0:21:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, Mara?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:58.08,0:22:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Mara, you saw Generalissimo Fract up close, didn't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:03.05,0:22:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What was he like?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:06.47,0:22:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. That similar, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:05.53,0:23:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for saving me.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:08.28,0:23:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in you now, Aide.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:18.71,0:23:22.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The state of Bjor has conquered\Nmost of the Old Continent.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:23.21,0:23:28.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,To resist its expansion, the remaining countries formed a coalition.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:28.42,0:23:35.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Bjor now had to live with the fact that\N the alliance was aiding Orthozes militarily. {they even messed up the map and orthozes moved one province to the left from the first episode lol}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.06,0:23:39.31,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A hurried meeting was called within Bjor.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:39.31,0:23:42.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The ministers had already reached a unanimous decision.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:42.19,0:23:46.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Orthozes invasion army \Nwould now be put on standby.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:47.03,0:23:47.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.65,0:23:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We will invade Orthozes, as planned.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.33,0:24:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,After coming this far, \Nis there anything we need to fear?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.92,0:24:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Our country chose the path of fighting.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:05.59,0:24:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We have always acted on the belief
Dialogue: 10,0:24:07.63,0:24:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that our nation can only have\N a future by winning in battle.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:12.97,0:24:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If we choose to back off now,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:15.72,0:24:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,our realm might crumble in an instant.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:19.77,0:24:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever considered that?! {lit: is it impossible to imagine for you gentlemen? - not sure what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:25.65,0:24:30.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Commander Fract's fiery speech \Nrekindled everyone's determination.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:31.11,0:24:33.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The result was a strong reminder
Dialogue: 10,0:24:33.91,0:24:38.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that a great empire \Nbuilt by fighting cannot prosper
Dialogue: 10,0:24:38.91,0:24:42.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,unless it continues to show off its strength.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:45.96,0:24:50.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,With this, I will become a king\N greater than my father.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:33.73,0:26:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bjor armies finally cross into Orthozes.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:37.70,0:26:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Dino, the fighting man,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:39.24,0:26:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is a legendary guerrilla fighter\N who has won many similar battles in the past.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:43.66,0:26:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But even he...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:44.45,0:26:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,did not choose to fight willingly.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:48.00,0:26:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, memories from the time of parting\N eat away at Dino's heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:53.00,0:26:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}Kingdom of Chaos: Born to Kill{\i0}. \NChapter 3: Dino.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:57.80,0:27:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Why are people born? Why do they die?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.88,0:02:37.22,Song,,0,0,0,,The ones we think of as beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.22,0:02:46.18,Song,,0,0,0,,Are not a simple coincidence or turn of fate
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.27,0:02:54.52,Song,,0,0,0,,I know where I am, what I'm doing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:03:03.62,Song,,0,0,0,,And what I like most, I suppose
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.70,0:03:12.75,Song,,0,0,0,,It's not simple, though
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.50,0:03:20.97,Song,,0,0,0,,Show me your many sides!\N I'll keep looking for you too
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.47,0:03:27.14,Song,,0,0,0,,Not needed by one, necessary for another
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.14,0:03:32.48,Song,,0,0,0,,In a city where buildings reflect light from all around
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:37.86,Song,,0,0,0,,There's a place designated just for you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.41,0:03:48.16,Song,,0,0,0,,May you find it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.16,0:03:52.62,Song,,0,0,0,,May it shine for you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.45,0:25:20.24,Song,,0,0,0,,Why can't time be captured in a bottle?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.24,0:25:27.67,Song,,0,0,0,,I guess we all grow up before we realize it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.21,0:25:37.30,Song,,0,0,0,,The sunset leaves shadows on your vacant desk
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.30,0:25:42.93,Song,,0,0,0,,The sun goes down as if giving up
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.93,0:25:48.10,Song,,0,0,0,,A dictionary full of pencil markings
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.40,0:25:57.32,Song,,0,0,0,,And torn into jagged pieces
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.57,0:26:05.08,Song,,0,0,0,,The wish that was scattered into the galaxy that day
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.08,0:26:12.38,Song,,0,0,0,,Will surely rise again, searching for you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.38,0:26:21.30,Song,,0,0,0,,Following an answer that no one knows, \Neven if it's hazy now
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.30,0:26:28.44,Song,,0,0,0,,Someday, it will shine straight toward the stars
